To Doc Del,<br><br>
Thanks for your comments. You have the nack of pulling on my rope at just the right time! I appreciate it and will work on your questions. They are well put. I will do this off line for a while.<br><br>
To Pointman:<br><br>
Your point of view on amnesty makes sense to me. I may share a similar view one day after this part of the process in my mind finishes its work and moves on to other things. We are all at somewhat different points in our thoughts, and that is why this dialog is so very important. The bits and pieces I pick up from others that fit in my puzzle always help to move me forward. <br><br>
I share your feelings that all we have is each other. That has been my personal experience. There are a few other things that have happened to me lately that are beginning to erode my view on that. I have discovered a few people out there who really do care. I am beginning to learn to work with that very new experience and feeling. It is scarey, but what the hell, I survived Nam, and I can survive this, too!<br><br>
Regards,<br><br>
Arthur  
